# Worktree isolation

Parallel milestones conflict when agents share paths or integration branches. Worktrees isolate **checkouts**, not **overlapping files**. Follow this policy on every task.

## Worktree map

| Worktree | Path | Purpose | Allowed branches |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Primary | `KalshiBot` | Dev server / read-only | `main` only — **no commits** |
| Builder 1 | `kalshi-builder1` | Feature milestones | `feature/*` |
| Builder 2 | `kalshi-builder2` | Feature milestones | `feature/*` |
| Builder 3 | `kalshi-builder3` | Feature milestones | `feature/*` |
| Builder 4 | `kalshi-builder4` | Feature milestones | `feature/*` |
| Review | `kalshi-review` | PR review + bugfixes | `review/*`, `fix/*` |

## Session start (required)

Before any edit or git command:

```bash
cd C:/Users/Kimmillie/kalshi-builder1   # or builder2/3/4; kalshi-review for review/bugfix work
git rev-parse --show-toplevel
git branch --show-current
git status --short
npm run worktree:assign -- <branch>
```

Abort if the prompt's worktree name does not match `show-toplevel`, or if the branch does not match the task.

## Branch assignment

Each worktree keeps a local `.worktree-branch` file (gitignored). Pre-commit **blocks** commits when the current branch differs from that file.

```bash
# Builder milestone
npm run worktree:assign -- feature/m6.24c-strategy-leaderboard

# Review / bugfix (use kalshi-review)
npm run worktree:assign -- fix/raw-ticker-ui-leak
```

Re-run when switching branches in the same worktree.

## Review and bugfix workflow

Bugfixes and PR review fixes belong in **`kalshi-review`**, not builder worktrees.

```bash
cd C:/Users/Kimmillie/kalshi-review
git fetch origin
git checkout -B fix/short-description origin/main
npm run worktree:assign -- fix/short-description
```

For fixes on an open PR branch:

```bash
git checkout -B review/m6.24c-pr-fixes origin/feature/m6.24c-strategy-leaderboard
npm run worktree:assign -- review/m6.24c-pr-fixes
```

## Forbidden

- Commits from `KalshiBot` (primary worktree)
- Bugfixes in `kalshi-builder1` / `kalshi-builder2` / `kalshi-builder3` / `kalshi-builder4` — use `kalshi-review`
- `git checkout main` inside a builder worktree (`main` is checked out in the primary worktree)
- `git merge`, `git cherry-pick`, or development on `merge/*` branches
- Reusing another builder's branch
- `git reset --hard` unless recovering from a confirmed mistake

## Starting a milestone (builders)

```bash
cd C:/Users/Kimmillie/kalshi-builder1   # or builder2, builder3, builder4
git fetch origin
git checkout -B feature/m6.XXy-slug origin/main
npm run worktree:assign -- feature/m6.XXy-slug
```

If the milestone depends on an unmerged branch, branch from that **named feature branch**, not a `merge/*` branch.

## Overlapping milestones

When parallel milestones touch the same modules:

1. Merge foundation milestones to `main` before starting dependents.
2. Rebase downstream feature branches onto updated `main`.
3. Keep file ownership in the prompt (only paths for the current milestone).

## Commit scope

- One task per branch
- Stage only files for that task
- Do not merge — open a PR instead
